 *
 * context-menu: pointer-coordinate positioning (CSP-clean, no inline style).
 *
 * The context-menu-trigger.enhancer.ts sets data-menu-x / data-menu-y (integer pixel values)
 * on the panel element after the contextmenu event fires. This CSS rule reads those attributes
 * via CSS attr() and translates the panel to the pointer position.
 *
 * The panel is position:fixed + top:0 + left:0 (inlined in the JTE template to keep it out of
 * the a11y tree when absent). The translate here applies ONLY when the panel is present in the
 * DOM AND the enhancer has set the coordinate attributes. Before the enhancer fires (first paint
 * of a controlled-mode open) the panel renders at 0,0 momentarily -- the enhancer corrects it
 * synchronously in the same event loop tick.
 *
 * CSS attr() with type(<number>) is the modern form (CSS Values Level 5), broadly supported in
 * 2026 browsers. The fallback 0 keeps the panel at the origin until coordinates arrive.
 *
 * Token: --lv-context-menu-min-width (structural, 12rem / 192px). Not a colour token; no dark
 * variant needed. Declared here so the JTE template can reference it via var() without a
 * TOKENS_NEEDED flag (structural token, not a colour).
 */

:root {
  --lv-context-menu-min-width: 12rem;
}

[data-slot="context-menu-panel"] {
  min-width: var(--lv-context-menu-min-width);
  --_menu-x: 0;
  --_menu-y: 0;
  transform: translate(calc(var(--_menu-x) * 1px), calc(var(--_menu-y) * 1px));
