  placeholders -- used by Facebook, YouTube, LinkedIn) instead of pulse, because shimmer signals
  "fetching from a distant source" more precisely than pulse and avoids the flicker effect on
  multi-row stacks at 60fps. Tokens (--lv-skeleton-bg, --lv-skeleton-shimmer) mean a retheme is
  a token override, not a template edit.

  SHAPE vocabulary: five presets cover the universal loading patterns.
    lines       -- N text rows with deterministic varying widths (no DB data, no RNG).
                   Widths cycle through ["100%","75%","88%","62%","94%"] by row index mod 5.
    card        -- a tall rectangular block (image/card thumb placeholder).
    avatar-row  -- a circle + two text lines side-by-side (user row placeholder).
    image       -- a wide shallow rectangle (hero image placeholder).
    button-bar  -- a single short rounded-full strip (button placeholder).

  SIZE scale: sm/md/lg scales the text-row height (lines shape only) and circle diameter
  (avatar-row shape only). card/image/button-bar have intrinsic proportions.

  A11y (WAI-ARIA): role="status" + aria-live="polite" + aria-atomic="true" on the root so
  assistive tech announces the busy state. aria-label carries the accessible label. A sr-only
  span carries the same text inside the live region for aria-atomic. The decorative bars are
  aria-hidden="true" (they are purely visual; the text label conveys all meaning).
  https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/status_role

  ANIMATION CSS: lives in skeleton.css (component-scoped). The .lv-skeleton--active class
  enables the shimmer gradient + keyframe on .lv-skeleton__bar; without it the bars are a
  static --lv-skeleton-bg fill. The reduced-motion override (@media prefers-reduced-motion)
  is in skeleton.css alongside the animation rule so the suppression is co-located with its cause.

  Params:
    String size          = "md"     "sm" | "md" | "lg" -- text-row height + avatar-row circle size.
    boolean active       = true     true: shimmer animation; false: static muted fill.
    int skeletonRows     = 3        lines shape: number of text placeholder rows.
    String skeletonShape = "lines"  "lines" | "card" | "avatar-row" | "image" | "button-bar".
    String label         = "Loading..."  accessible name; sr-only.
    String cssClass      = ""       extra utility classes on the root.
    String attrs         = ""       TRUSTED raw ($unsafe) -- STATIC author-typed strings only.
    Map<String,String> dataAttrs = {}  SAFE dynamic data-* (value escaped via Escape.htmlAttribute).

  Usage:
    @@template.lievit.skeleton()
    @@template.lievit.skeleton(skeletonShape = "avatar-row", active = false)
    @@template.lievit.skeleton(skeletonRows = 5, size = "sm")
--%>
@param String size = "md"
@param boolean active = true
@param int skeletonRows = 3
@param String skeletonShape = "lines"
@param String label = "Loading…"
@param String cssClass = ""
@param String attrs = ""
@param java.util.Map<String, String> dataAttrs = java.util.Map.of()

!{var activeClass = active ? "lv-skeleton--active" : "";}
!{var lineHeights = java.util.Map.of("sm", "0.75rem", "md", "1rem", "lg", "1.25rem");}
!{var lineH = lineHeights.getOrDefault(size, "1rem");}
<%-- Deterministic width sequence: no DB data, no RNG; cycles by row index mod 5. --%>
!{var widths = java.util.List.of("100%", "75%", "88%", "62%", "94%");}

!{var dataAttrs_ = new StringOutput();}
!{for (var e : dataAttrs.entrySet()) {
    if (e.getKey() != null && e.getKey().matches("[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9-]*")) {
      dataAttrs_.writeContent(" data-" + e.getKey() + "=\"");
      Escape.htmlAttribute(e.getValue() == null ? "" : e.getValue(), dataAttrs_);
      dataAttrs_.writeContent("\"");
    }
  }}
!{var dataAttrsMarkup = dataAttrs_.toString();}

<div
  role="status"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-atomic="true"
  aria-label="${label}"
  data-slot="loading-section"
  data-mode="skeleton"
  data-shape="${skeletonShape}"
  data-size="${size}"
  data-active="${active ? "true" : "false"}"
  class="lv-skeleton ${activeClass} ${cssClass}"
  $unsafe{dataAttrsMarkup}
  $unsafe{attrs}
>
  <span class="sr-only">${label}</span>

  @if("lines".equals(skeletonShape))
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="lv-skeleton__lines flex flex-col" style="gap: var(--lv-space-2);">
      @for(int i = 0; i < skeletonRows; i++)
        <div
          class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)]"
          style="height:${lineH};width:${widths.get(i % widths.size())};"
        ></div>
      @endfor
    </div>
  @elseif("card".equals(skeletonShape))
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)]" style="width:100%;height:12rem;"></div>
  @elseif("avatar-row".equals(skeletonShape))
    !{var avatarSize = "sm".equals(size) ? "2rem" : "lg".equals(size) ? "3rem" : "2.5rem";}
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="lv-skeleton__avatar-row flex items-center" style="gap: var(--lv-space-3);">
      <div class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)]" style="width:${avatarSize};height:${avatarSize};flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div class="flex flex-col" style="gap: var(--lv-space-2); flex:1;">
        <div class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)]" style="height:${lineH};width:60%;"></div>
        <div class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)]" style="height:${lineH};width:40%;"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  @elseif("image".equals(skeletonShape))
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)]" style="width:100%;height:6rem;"></div>
  @elseif("button-bar".equals(skeletonShape))
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="lv-skeleton__bar rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)]" style="width:8rem;height:2.25rem;"></div>
  @endif
</div>

/*
 * Copyright 2026 Francesco Bilotta
 * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License").
 *
 * lievit-ui skeleton component CSS.
 *
 * The shimmer animation and reduced-motion suppression are co-located here so the
 * suppression rule lives next to the cause. All selector names carry the lv-skeleton
 * prefix (namespaced, greppable). The keyframe is declared in lievit-tokens.css
 * (lv-skeleton-shimmer) alongside the other lv-* keyframes.
 *
 * Tokens consumed: --lv-skeleton-bg, --lv-skeleton-shimmer (net-new, loading-section spec §5).
 */

/* Static fill: applied to every bar regardless of active state. */
.lv-skeleton__bar {
  background: var(--lv-skeleton-bg);
}

/* Shimmer: gradient + animation when the parent carries lv-skeleton--active. */
.lv-skeleton--active .lv-skeleton__bar {
  background: linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    var(--lv-skeleton-bg)      25%,
    var(--lv-skeleton-shimmer) 50%,
    var(--lv-skeleton-bg)      75%
  );
  background-size: 400% 100%;
  animation: lv-skeleton-shimmer 1.5s var(--lv-motion-easing-in-out, ease-in-out) infinite;
}

/* Reduced motion: collapse to static fill, no animation. */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .lv-skeleton--active .lv-skeleton__bar {
    animation: none;
    background: var(--lv-skeleton-bg);
  }
}

@import gg.jte.Content
<%--
  Copyright 2026 Francesco Bilotta
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License").

  lievit-ui slide-over partial -- the STATIC shadcn Sheet: a modal panel that slides in from a viewport
  edge (right | left | top | bottom), trigger-driven, with ZERO shipped JS. It is the modal partial
  pinned to an edge instead of centred: same native <dialog> seam (top-layer, browser focus-trap,
  ::backdrop, Escape light-dismiss, AT-modal), so it too is CSP-clean by construction with no
  enhancer.

  TIER: STATIC presentational -> JTE partial. Distinct from the WIRE drawer / sheet
  (registry/wire/drawer/, registry/wire/sheet/): those hold `open` server-side (a @Wire boolean) for
  flows where the server owns open-state (and the SlideOver "view in panel" outcome builds on the
  drawer wire). THIS partial is the trigger-driven static case -- the open-state is the browser's
  <dialog>, opened by the trigger, closed by the close button / backdrop / Escape, no round-trip.

  SERVES THE KIT: this is the static presentation shell behind the kit's edge-anchored panels --
  dev.lievit.kit.SlideOver (a right-anchored detail panel; side="right") and any ModalConfig with
  asSlideOver() (Filament slide-over, side defaults right, width full). The `side` left/right/top/
  bottom matches the kit/shadcn Sheet sides; data-side mirrors it for styling + testing.

  SHOW/HIDE (native, zero JS), identical to the modal partial:
    - OPEN  = <button command="show-modal" commandfor="${id}"> opens the <dialog> as a modal.
    - CLOSE = <form method="dialog"> close affordances: header close (x), backdrop, Escape (native).
  The only difference from the modal is the panel POSITION: instead of centring, the <dialog> is
  pinned to the chosen edge and sized to span the cross axis (a side sheet is full-height + a fixed
  inline width; a top/bottom sheet is full-width + a fixed block height).

  BACKDROP DISMISS (closeByClickingAway / shadcn outside-click close): a full-bleed
  <form method="dialog"><button data-slot="sheet-backdrop"> behind the content closes on click.

  A11y (WAI-ARIA APG Dialog/Modal via native <dialog>): showModal() makes it a modal dialog to AT;
  we also stamp role="dialog" + aria-modal="true" + aria-labelledby (the heading id, else
  aria-label) + aria-describedby (the description id when present). Browser traps focus + returns it
  to the trigger on close.

  Params:
    String         id = "lv-slide-over"   the <dialog> id (the commandfor target). Unique per page.
    gg.jte.Content trigger                 the trigger CONTENT inside the <button>.
    gg.jte.Content content                 the panel body, OWNED + server-rendered (never a <slot>).
    String         side = "right"          "right" | "left" | "top" | "bottom": the edge it slides from.
    String         heading = null          the panel title; renders SheetHeader + SheetTitle, wires aria-labelledby.
    String         description = null       supporting line; renders SheetDescription, wires aria-describedby.
    gg.jte.Content footer = null           the footer region (SheetFooter): actions pinned at the panel end.
    boolean        closeButton = true      render the top-right close (x) button.
    boolean        closeByClickingAway = true  a backdrop click closes the panel.
    String         cssClass = ""           extra utility classes on the wrapper.

  Usage:
    @@template.lievit.slide-over(
      id = "view-panel",
      side = "right",
      trigger = @@`View`,
      heading = "Record detail",
      content = @@`<dl>...the infolist...</dl>`
    )
--%>
@param String id = "lv-slide-over"
@param gg.jte.Content trigger
@param gg.jte.Content content
@param String side = "right"
@param String heading = null
@param String description = null
@param gg.jte.Content footer = null
@param boolean closeButton = true
@param boolean closeByClickingAway = true
@param String cssClass = ""
!{var titleId = id + "-title";}
!{var descId = id + "-description";}
!{var hasHeading = heading != null && !heading.isEmpty();}
!{var hasDesc = description != null && !description.isEmpty();}
!{var edge = switch (side) {
    case "left", "top", "bottom" -> side;
    default -> "right";
  };}
!{var panelPos = switch (edge) {
    case "left" -> "inset:0 auto 0 0; height:100dvh; width:min(90vw,24rem); border-right:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);";
    case "top" -> "inset:0 0 auto 0; width:100vw; max-height:85dvh; border-bottom:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);";
    case "bottom" -> "inset:auto 0 0 0; width:100vw; max-height:85dvh; border-top:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);";
    default -> "inset:0 0 0 auto; height:100dvh; width:min(90vw,24rem); border-left:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);";
  };}

<span data-slot="sheet" class="inline-block ${cssClass}" style="font-family:var(--lv-font-sans);">
  <button
    type="button"
    data-slot="sheet-trigger"
    command="show-modal"
    commandfor="${id}"
    class="inline-flex items-center gap-[var(--lv-space-1)] rounded-[var(--lv-radius-md)] border border-[var(--lv-color-border)] bg-[var(--lv-color-bg)] px-[var(--lv-space-3)] py-[var(--lv-space-2)] text-[length:var(--lv-text-sm)] text-[var(--lv-color-fg)] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)]"
  >${trigger}</button>

  <dialog
    id="${id}"
    data-slot="sheet-content"
    data-side="${edge}"
    role="dialog"
    aria-modal="true"
    aria-labelledby="${hasHeading ? titleId : null}"
    aria-describedby="${hasDesc ? descId : null}"
    aria-label="${hasHeading ? null : "Sheet"}"
    class="m-0 box-border flex max-w-none flex-col border-0 bg-[var(--lv-color-bg)] p-0 text-[var(--lv-color-fg)] shadow-[var(--lv-shadow-lg)]"
    style="${panelPos} z-index:var(--lv-z-modal); font-family:var(--lv-font-sans);"
  >
    @if(closeByClickingAway)
      <form method="dialog" data-slot="sheet-backdrop-form">
        <button
          type="submit"
          data-slot="sheet-backdrop"
          aria-label="Close"
          class="fixed inset-0 -z-[1] block h-full w-full cursor-default border-0 bg-transparent p-0"
        ></button>
      </form>
    @endif

    @if(hasHeading || closeButton)
      <div data-slot="sheet-header" class="flex items-start justify-between gap-[var(--lv-space-3)] p-[var(--lv-space-4)]">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-[var(--lv-space-1)]">
          @if(hasHeading)
            <h2 data-slot="sheet-title" id="${titleId}" class="m-0 text-[length:var(--lv-text-lg)] font-[var(--lv-font-semibold)] leading-[var(--lv-leading-tight)] text-[var(--lv-color-fg)]">${heading}</h2>
          @endif
          @if(hasDesc)
            <p data-slot="sheet-description" id="${descId}" class="m-0 text-[length:var(--lv-text-sm)] leading-[var(--lv-leading)] text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)]">${description}</p>
          @endif
        </div>
        @if(closeButton)
          <form method="dialog" class="contents">
            <button
              type="submit"
              data-slot="sheet-close"
              aria-label="Close"
              class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center rounded-[var(--lv-radius-sm)] border-0 bg-transparent p-[var(--lv-space-1)] leading-none text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)]"
            >@template.lievit.icon(name = "x", size = "1rem")</button>
          </form>
        @endif
      </div>
    @endif

    <div data-slot="sheet-body" class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-[var(--lv-space-4)] text-[length:var(--lv-text-base)] leading-[var(--lv-leading)] text-[var(--lv-color-fg)]">
      ${content}
    </div>

    @if(footer != null)
      <div data-slot="sheet-footer" class="mt-auto flex flex-col gap-[var(--lv-space-2)] p-[var(--lv-space-4)]">
        ${footer}
      </div>
    @endif
  </dialog>
</span>

@import gg.jte.Content
@import gg.jte.output.StringOutput
@import gg.jte.html.escape.Escape
<%--
  Copyright 2026 Francesco Bilotta
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License").

  lievit-ui stat-card partial -- single-metric KPI display card: prominent label + value + optional
  trend indicator (direction + delta magnitude) + leading/trailing/footer slots + optional link wrapper.

  TIER: PARTIAL -- purely presentational; zero client state, fires no actions. The server computes
  and pre-formats the value; this partial renders it. htmx refresh on the card is an adopter concern
  wired through the attrs channel; this partial ships no timing logic of its own.

  STRUCTURE (scientific decision rule): no WAI-ARIA APG composite pattern applies to a pure static
  numeric display card (APG patterns index verified at https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/;
  the applicable norms are WCAG 2.2 SC 1.1.1, SC 1.4.3, and SC 4.1.2). The root element is figure,
  the HTML5 element for self-contained content with its caption -- the correct semantic container for
  a metric tile (title = figcaption, value = the metric illustration). Ant Design Statistic consulted
  as feature inventory (value, title, prefix/suffix, precision, trend direction+value, loading state,
  card layout); Tailwind UI Stats / KPI card patterns consulted for visual layout vocabulary.
  Styling is original generation over --lv-* tokens (no code copied from any reference).

  TOKEN NOTE: --lv-text-4xl does not exist in lievit-tokens.css (the scale stops at --lv-text-3xl
  as of this writing). The spec mandates it for size="lg"; the token is emitted as-is per the spec
  to be wire-compatible when the token ships. The fallback when the token is undefined is no
  font-size change (CSS ignores an unknown var() fallback cascade). If the visual result is wrong
  in the interim, define the token or use size="md" and override with cssClass / inline style.

  A11y (WCAG 2.2; no WAI-ARIA APG pattern -- pure display element):
    - Non-linked card: figure[aria-labelledby=titleId] root; figcaption[id=titleId] = metric label.
      Screen reader announces the label on figure entry, then reads value/trend/description in order.
    - Linked card: a[aria-label="title: prefix value suffix"] wrapping figure[aria-hidden="true"].
      The inner figure is aria-hidden to avoid double-announcing the inner structure.
    - Value: p[data-slot=stat-card-value][aria-atomic="true"] so HTMX morph triggers a full re-read.
    - Prefix / suffix: span[aria-hidden="true"] (decorative symbols; meaning carried by value text
      and by the a[aria-label] on linked cards).
    - Trend indicator: span[role="img"][aria-label="Tendenza: in aumento, +12 %"] -- direction AND
      magnitude communicated textually, never by colour alone (WCAG SC 1.4.1 + 4.1.2). Inline trend
      SVG icons carry aria-hidden="true" (decorative; meaning is in the parent role=img label).
    - Loading state: aria-busy="true" on the root figure; skeleton bars aria-hidden="true".
    - Footer hr: role="separator" aria-hidden="true" (decorative divider, suppressed from SR).
    - Leading slot: div[aria-hidden="true"] (the slot is decorative; adopter supplies accessible
      names for any meaningful icon or avatar placed here).
    - Trailing slot: div (no aria-hidden -- adopter may place interactive elements with own names).
    - No focus trap, no roving tabindex, no initial focus steal, no live region: display only.
    - Link card focus ring: the native a element receives platform focus; --lv-ring provides the ring.

  Params:
    String title            (required) metric label (e.g. "Nuovi contatti"); becomes the figure
                            accessible name via aria-labelledby. Rendered above the value.
    String value            (required) pre-formatted metric value (e.g. "1 284", "92,4 %"). The
                            controller owns number formatting + locale; the partial is a dumb renderer.
    String prefix       = "" symbol displayed immediately before the value (e.g. "EUR", "#"); decorative.
    String suffix       = "" symbol displayed immediately after the value (e.g. "%", "k"); decorative.
    String description  = "" secondary line below trend: context, period, or source note; empty omits it.
    String trend        = "none" up | down | neutral | none -- direction of the trend indicator and
                            its intent colour (up=success green, down=destructive red, neutral=muted).
    String trendValue   = "" delta text alongside the trend icon (e.g. "+12 %", "-340 EUR").
    String trendLabel   = "" screen-reader label override for the trend span[role=img]; when empty the
                            auto-generated "Tendenza: in aumento, +12 %" label is used.
    boolean loading     = false skeleton state: replaces value + trend with animated placeholder bars;
                            emits aria-busy="true" on the root figure.
    String size         = "md" sm | md | lg -- scales the value font size and card padding only
                            (display component, NOT toolbar-height aligned; architecture contract 5b).
    String variant      = "default" default | info | success | warning | destructive -- controls the
                            decorative left-border accent colour only; does not recolour the value text.
                            "plain" drops the 3px left rail entirely (uniform 1px border, the mock's
                            railless KPI card with a top-right icon chip + footer sparkline).
    String href         = null when set, wraps the card in an a[href] making it a navigable link;
                            the a carries aria-label derived from title + prefix + value + suffix.
    gg.jte.Content leading  = null icon / avatar / pictogram to the left of the title+value column.
    gg.jte.Content trailing = null top-right corner content (period badge, settings icon button, etc.).
    gg.jte.Content footer   = null ruled bottom section (sparkline, comparison bar, detail link row).
    String cssClass     = "" extra utility classes appended to the card root element.
    String attrs        = "" TRUSTED raw ($unsafe) -- STATIC author-typed strings only (data-testid,
                            HTMX directives). Never feed a per-row DB-derived value through this channel.
    Map<String,String> dataAttrs = {} SAFE escaped dynamic data-* attributes (values via Escape.htmlAttribute).
                            Use for per-row identifiers when the card appears inside a loop.

  Usage:
    @@template.lievit.stat-card(title = "Nuovi contatti", value = "284")
    @@template.lievit.stat-card(
      title = "Ricavi mensili", value = "38 000", prefix = "EUR",
      trend = "up", trendValue = "+12 %",
      variant = "success", size = "lg",
      attrs = "hx-get=\"/stats/revenue\" hx-trigger=\"every 30s\" hx-target=\"this\" hx-swap=\"outerHTML\"")
--%>
@param String title
@param String value
@param String prefix = ""
@param String suffix = ""
@param String description = ""
@param String trend = "none"
@param String trendValue = ""
@param String trendLabel = ""
@param boolean loading = false
@param String size = "md"
@param String variant = "default"
@param String href = null
@param gg.jte.Content leading = null
@param gg.jte.Content trailing = null
@param gg.jte.Content footer = null
@param String cssClass = ""
@param String attrs = ""
@param java.util.Map<String, String> dataAttrs = java.util.Map.of()

!{var _titleId = "sc-" + Integer.toHexString(title.hashCode());}
!{var _isLink = href != null && !href.isBlank();}
!{var _hasTrend = !"none".equals(trend);}
!{var _hasDescription = !description.isBlank();}
!{var _hasLeading = leading != null;}
!{var _hasTrailing = trailing != null;}
!{var _hasFooter = footer != null;}
<%-- size: value font-size + card padding. See TOKEN NOTE above re: --lv-text-4xl. --%>
!{var _sizeValue = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "var(--lv-text-2xl)";
    case "lg" -> "var(--lv-text-4xl)";
    default   -> "var(--lv-text-3xl)";
  };}
!{var _sizePad = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "var(--lv-space-4)";
    case "lg" -> "var(--lv-space-6)";
    default   -> "var(--lv-space-5)";
  };}
<%-- variant: left-border accent colour only. "default" keeps the border transparent. --%>
!{var _accentColor = switch (variant) {
    case "info"        -> "var(--lv-color-info)";
    case "success"     -> "var(--lv-color-success)";
    case "warning"     -> "var(--lv-color-warning)";
    case "destructive" -> "var(--lv-color-destructive)";
    default            -> "transparent";
  };}
<%-- trend: intent colour + auto-generated accessible label (direction + magnitude in Italian). --%>
!{var _trendColor = switch (trend) {
    case "up"   -> "var(--lv-color-success)";
    case "down" -> "var(--lv-color-destructive)";
    default     -> "var(--lv-color-muted-fg)";
  };}
!{var _autoTrendLabel = switch (trend) {
    case "up"   -> "Tendenza: in aumento" + (trendValue.isBlank() ? "" : ", " + trendValue);
    case "down" -> "Tendenza: in calo"    + (trendValue.isBlank() ? "" : ", " + trendValue);
    default     -> "Tendenza: stabile"    + (trendValue.isBlank() ? "" : ", " + trendValue);
  };}
!{var _effectiveTrendLabel = trendLabel.isBlank() ? _autoTrendLabel : trendLabel;}
<%-- linked card: full accessible name on the a element (prefix+value+suffix conveyed in text). --%>
!{var _linkLabel = title + ": " + prefix + value + suffix;}
<%-- left accent rail: every variant draws a 3px left border (transparent for "default"); the
     "plain" variant drops the rail entirely for a uniform 1px border on all four sides (the mock's
     stat cards have no left rail, just border + shadow + a top-right icon chip). --%>
!{var _leftRail = "plain".equals(variant) ? "" : "border-left-width:3px;border-left-color:" + _accentColor + ";";}
<%-- card shell style: token-driven, no hardcoded colours. --%>
!{var _cardStyle = "font-family:var(--lv-font-sans);padding:" + _sizePad + ";border-radius:var(--lv-radius-lg);border:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);" + _leftRail + "background:var(--lv-color-card);color:var(--lv-color-card-fg);box-shadow:var(--lv-shadow-sm);";}

<%-- SAFE dynamic data-* attributes: keys allowlisted to simple identifiers ([A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9-]*);
     values escaped via Escape.htmlAttribute. JTE's HTML parser forbids a raw @for in attribute-NAME
     position, so the fragment is built once here and emitted with $unsafe. --%>
!{var _dataAttrs_ = new StringOutput();}
!{for (var _e : dataAttrs.entrySet()) {
    if (_e.getKey() != null && _e.getKey().matches("[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9-]*")) {
      _dataAttrs_.writeContent(" data-" + _e.getKey() + "=\"");
      Escape.htmlAttribute(_e.getValue() == null ? "" : _e.getValue(), _dataAttrs_);
      _dataAttrs_.writeContent("\"");
    }
  }}
!{var _dataAttrsMarkup = _dataAttrs_.toString();}

<%-- figure is ALWAYS the semantic root (aria-labelledby ties it to its figcaption); when href is
     set, a stretched-link <a> overlays the whole card (position:relative on the figure + absolute
     inset-0 on the a). This keeps every tag balanced within one static branch (JTE HTML checker)
     and is the canonical accessible card-link pattern. loading=true sets aria-busy on the figure. --%>
<figure
  data-slot="stat-card"
  data-variant="${variant}"
  data-size="${size}"
  aria-labelledby="${_titleId}"
  aria-busy="${loading ? "true" : null}"
  class="${cssClass}"
  style="${_cardStyle}display:flex;flex-direction:column;${_isLink ? "position:relative;" : ""}"
  $unsafe{attrs}
  $unsafe{_dataAttrsMarkup}
>
@if(_isLink)
  <a
    href="${href}"
    data-slot="stat-card-link"
    aria-label="${_linkLabel}"
    class="absolute inset-0 rounded-[var(--lv-radius-lg)] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)]"
    style="z-index:1;"
  ></a>
@endif

  <%-- Header row: title + optional leading/trailing layout. --%>
  <div data-slot="stat-card-header" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:var(--lv-space-3);">
    @if(_hasLeading)
    <%-- leading slot: aria-hidden -- the slot is decorative (icon, avatar, pictogram).
         Adopter must supply accessible names for any meaningful content placed here. --%>
    <div data-slot="stat-card-leading" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink:0;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;color:var(--lv-color-muted-fg);">
      ${leading}
    </div>
    @endif
    <div style="flex:1 1 0%;min-width:0;">
      @if(!_isLink)
      <%-- figcaption id is the target of the figure's aria-labelledby; emitted only when not linked
           because the linked figure is aria-hidden and needs no labelledby. --%>
      <figcaption
        id="${_titleId}"
        data-slot="stat-card-title"
        style="margin:0;font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);font-weight:var(--lv-font-medium);color:var(--lv-color-muted-fg);line-height:1;"
      >${title}</figcaption>
      @else
      <figcaption
        data-slot="stat-card-title"
        style="margin:0;font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);font-weight:var(--lv-font-medium);color:var(--lv-color-muted-fg);line-height:1;"
      >${title}</figcaption>
      @endif
    </div>
    @if(_hasTrailing)
    <%-- trailing slot: NOT aria-hidden -- adopter may place interactive elements here. --%>
    <div data-slot="stat-card-trailing" style="flex-shrink:0;">
      ${trailing}
    </div>
    @endif
  </div>

  <%-- Body: value row (or skeleton) + trend indicator + description. --%>
  @if(loading)
  <%-- Skeleton state: animated placeholder bars replace value + trend. The root figure already
       carries aria-busy="true"; bars are aria-hidden so the SR does not announce "placeholder". --%>
  <div data-slot="stat-card-skeleton" aria-hidden="true" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--lv-space-2);margin-top:var(--lv-space-3);">
    <span style="display:block;height:2rem;width:50%;border-radius:var(--lv-radius-sm);background:var(--lv-color-muted-bg);animation:pulse 2s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.6,1) infinite;"></span>
    <span style="display:block;height:1rem;width:33%;border-radius:var(--lv-radius-sm);background:var(--lv-color-muted-bg);animation:pulse 2s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.6,1) infinite;"></span>
  </div>
  @else
  <%-- Value row: prefix (decorative, aria-hidden) + value + suffix (decorative, aria-hidden).
       aria-atomic="true" on the value p ensures HTMX morph re-announces the full value. --%>
  <div data-slot="stat-card-value-row" style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:var(--lv-space-1);margin-top:var(--lv-space-3);">
    @if(!prefix.isBlank())
    <span aria-hidden="true" data-slot="stat-card-prefix" style="font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);font-weight:var(--lv-font-medium);color:var(--lv-color-fg);">${prefix}</span>
    @endif
    <p
      data-slot="stat-card-value"
      aria-atomic="true"
      style="margin:0;font-size:${_sizeValue};font-weight:var(--lv-font-semibold);line-height:1;letter-spacing:-0.025em;color:var(--lv-color-fg);"
    >${value}</p>
    @if(!suffix.isBlank())
    <span aria-hidden="true" data-slot="stat-card-suffix" style="font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);font-weight:var(--lv-font-medium);color:var(--lv-color-fg);">${suffix}</span>
    @endif
  </div>

  @if(_hasTrend)
  <%-- Trend indicator: role="img" with aria-label carries the semantic (direction + magnitude).
       The SVG icon is aria-hidden (decorative; the role=img label is the a11y signal).
       Colour alone never conveys the trend direction (WCAG SC 1.4.1 + 4.1.2). --%>
  <div data-slot="stat-card-trend" data-trend="${trend}" style="margin-top:var(--lv-space-2);">
    <span
      role="img"
      aria-label="${_effectiveTrendLabel}"
      style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--lv-space-1);font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);font-weight:var(--lv-font-medium);color:${_trendColor};"
    >
      @if("up".equals(trend))
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1rem" height="1rem" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="18 15 12 9 6 15"></polyline></svg>
      @elseif("down".equals(trend))
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1rem" height="1rem" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
      @else
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1rem" height="1rem" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line></svg>
      @endif
      @if(!trendValue.isBlank())
      <%-- trendValue is inside the role=img span and so audibly implied by the aria-label;
           the span is aria-hidden to avoid double-reading by SR (aria-label is the authority). --%>
      <span aria-hidden="true">${trendValue}</span>
      @endif
    </span>
  </div>
  @endif

  @if(_hasDescription)
  <p data-slot="stat-card-description" style="margin:var(--lv-space-1) 0 0;font-size:var(--lv-text-sm);color:var(--lv-color-muted-fg);line-height:var(--lv-leading);">${description}</p>
  @endif
  @endif

  @if(_hasFooter)
  <%-- Footer: decorative rule + content slot. The hr carries role="separator" aria-hidden="true"
       so the SR does not announce a blank "separator" interrupting the reading flow of the card. --%>
  <hr role="separator" aria-hidden="true" style="margin:var(--lv-space-3) 0 0;border:0;border-top:1px solid var(--lv-color-border);">
  <div data-slot="stat-card-footer" style="margin-top:var(--lv-space-3);">
    ${footer}
  </div>
  @endif

</figure>

@import gg.jte.Content
@import gg.jte.output.StringOutput
@import gg.jte.html.escape.Escape
<%--
  Copyright 2026 Francesco Bilotta
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License").

  lievit-ui switch partial -- a native <button role="switch"> (or <input type="checkbox" role="switch">)
  styled as a sliding toggle control.

  TIER: STATIC presentational -> JTE partial. The control holds NO state of its own: the consuming
  WIRE template owns the checked state and wires the toggle via `wireClick`. Server-first works
  trivially here -- there is nothing irreducibly client about a binary toggle.

  STRUCTURE (scientific decision rule): a real native <button role="switch"> is the primary variant,
  following the WAI-ARIA APG Switch button-based example
  (https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/examples/switch-button/).
  The native <button> gives role + Enter/Space activation + focus for free; no JS enhancer is needed.
  The asCheckbox=true variant uses <input type="checkbox" role="switch"> for form submission.
  Both are CSP-clean: the thumb slide is driven entirely by CSS with zero JS.
  Button variant: data-checked on the button element drives data-[checked=true]: selectors on the thumb.
  Checkbox variant: the `peer` class on the input drives peer-checked: selectors on the sibling thumb.
  All Tailwind utility classes in !{var ...} blocks are COMPLETE static strings so the scanner picks them up.

  A11y (WAI-ARIA APG Switch, https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/):
    - button variant: <button role="switch" aria-checked="true|false">; Enter + Space toggle via platform.
    - checkbox variant: <input type="checkbox" role="switch">; Space toggles via platform; Enter submits form.
    - accessible name: ariaLabel > ariaLabelledBy > visible adjacent label (leading/trailing slot).
      A switch WITHOUT an accessible name is an a11y violation; the axe-core acceptance test asserts it.
    - on/off inner labels: aria-hidden="true" to avoid "On On" / "Off Off" double-announcement.
    - loading: aria-busy="true" on the interactive element; spinner inside the thumb.
    - disabled: native `disabled` attribute on <button>/<input> (NOT aria-disabled, which is for <a>).
    - aria-invalid: applied by the consuming `field` partial on the wrapper; the switch inherits via
      a CSS [aria-invalid] selector; the switch itself never emits aria-invalid.
    - focus-visible ring via --lv-ring on the interactive element (:focus-visible, NOT :focus).
    - No focus trap; no roving tabindex; no enhancer needed.

  SIZE (toolbar-aligned per architecture contract §5.b):
    sm  -> track 32x18px, thumb 14px (--lv-space-5)
    md  -> track 40x22px, thumb 18px (--lv-space-6) -- default + shadcn baseline
    lg  -> track 50x28px, thumb 22px (--lv-space-7)
  Track sizes are design invariants; thumb diameters use --lv-space-* tokens for on-grid sizing.
  Thumb translate = track-width - thumb-diameter - (track-height - thumb-diameter):
    sm: 32 - 14 - (18-14) = 14px; md: 40 - 18 - (22-18) = 18px; lg: 50 - 22 - (28-22) = 22px.

  WIRE / ESCAPING (verbatim from button.jte; the XSS decision rule):
    attrs     = TRUSTED raw ($unsafe) -- STATIC, author-typed strings ONLY (wire directives, form attr).
                NEVER interpolate a user/DB-derived value into attrs.
    dataAttrs = SAFE escaped Map<String,String>: each value through Escape.htmlAttribute.
    wireClick = SAFE wire action name, emitted as l:click="${wireClick}" (JTE escapes the attribute value).
    wireArgs  = SAFE per-row wire args: each emitted as data-<key>="<escaped-value>", merged with dataAttrs.
    A per-row, DB-derived value (e.g. entity id) goes through wireArgs, NEVER attrs.

  Params:
    boolean checked          = false   current on/off state (server truth; always a WIRE field reflection).
    String  size             = "md"    sm | md | lg -- height-based, toolbar-aligned.
    boolean disabled         = false   dims + blocks activation; native disabled on the element.
    boolean loading          = false   spinner in the thumb, aria-busy="true", blocks activation.
    boolean asCheckbox       = false   render <input type="checkbox" role="switch"> instead of <button>.
    String  name             = null    name attribute when asCheckbox=true.
    String  value            = "on"    value attribute when asCheckbox=true.
    String  ariaLabel        = null    aria-label; REQUIRED when no visible adjacent label exists.
    String  ariaLabelledBy   = null    aria-labelledby referencing an external label/heading element.
    String  ariaDescribedBy  = null    aria-describedby referencing a hint/description element.
    String  onLabel          = null    text inside the track when checked (Ant Design inner-label style);
                                       aria-hidden -- does NOT provide the accessible name.
    String  offLabel         = null    text inside the track when NOT checked; likewise aria-hidden.
    String  cssClass         = ""      extra utility classes appended to the root wrapper element.
    String  attrs            = ""      TRUSTED raw attribute string ($unsafe) -- STATIC strings only.
    java.util.Map<String, String> dataAttrs = java.util.Map.of()  SAFE dynamic data-* (each value escaped).
    String  wireClick        = null    SAFE wire action name; emitted as l:click="${wireClick}" when set.
    java.util.Map<String, String> wireArgs = java.util.Map.of()  SAFE per-row args merged into escaped data-*.
    gg.jte.Content leading   = null    slot rendered BEFORE the track (icon or label text).
    gg.jte.Content trailing  = null    slot rendered AFTER the track (most common visible label position).

  Usage:
    @@template.lievit.switch(checked = prefs.notifications(), ariaLabelledBy = "notifications-label",
        wireClick = "toggleNotifications", wireArgs = java.util.Map.of("userId", _instance.userId()))
    @@template.lievit.switch(checked = settings.darkMode(), ariaLabel = "Dark mode",
        trailing = @@`<span>Dark mode</span>`)
    @@template.lievit.switch(asCheckbox = true, name = "subscribe", checked = user.subscribed(),
        trailing = @@`<span>Subscribe to newsletter</span>`)
--%>
@param boolean checked = false
@param String size = "md"
@param boolean disabled = false
@param boolean loading = false
@param boolean asCheckbox = false
@param String name = null
@param String value = "on"
@param String ariaLabel = null
@param String ariaLabelledBy = null
@param String ariaDescribedBy = null
@param String onLabel = null
@param String offLabel = null
@param String cssClass = ""
@param String attrs = ""
@param java.util.Map<String, String> dataAttrs = java.util.Map.of()
@param String wireClick = null
@param java.util.Map<String, String> wireArgs = java.util.Map.of()
@param gg.jte.Content leading = null
@param gg.jte.Content trailing = null

<%-- Track dimensions -- COMPLETE static strings (Tailwind scanner requirement).
     sm: h-[18px] w-[32px];  md: h-[22px] w-[40px];  lg: h-[28px] w-[50px] --%>
!{var trackClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "h-[18px] w-[32px]";
    case "lg" -> "h-[28px] w-[50px]";
    default   -> "h-[22px] w-[40px]";
  };}

<%-- Thumb size using the spacing token (on-grid diameter). --%>
!{var thumbClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "size-[var(--lv-space-5)]";
    case "lg" -> "size-[var(--lv-space-7)]";
    default   -> "size-[var(--lv-space-6)]";
  };}

<%-- Button variant: [[data-checked=true]_&]: targets an ANCESTOR with data-checked=true (the <button>).
     This drives translate + colour on the thumb child. All class strings are COMPLETE + static. --%>
!{var thumbButtonCheckedClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "[[data-checked=true]_&]:translate-x-[14px] [[data-checked=true]_&]:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
    case "lg" -> "[[data-checked=true]_&]:translate-x-[22px] [[data-checked=true]_&]:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
    default   -> "[[data-checked=true]_&]:translate-x-[18px] [[data-checked=true]_&]:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
  };}

<%-- Checkbox variant: peer-checked: from the <input class="peer"> sibling drives translate + colour. --%>
!{var thumbCheckboxCheckedClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "peer-checked:translate-x-[14px] peer-checked:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
    case "lg" -> "peer-checked:translate-x-[22px] peer-checked:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
    default   -> "peer-checked:translate-x-[18px] peer-checked:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)]";
  };}

<%-- Inner on-label left offset = 2px gap + thumb-diameter; COMPLETE static strings. --%>
!{var onLabelLeft = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "left-[18px]";
    case "lg" -> "left-[26px]";
    default   -> "left-[22px]";
  };}

!{var innerLabelSize = "sm".equals(size)
    ? "text-[length:var(--lv-text-xs)]"
    : "text-[length:var(--lv-text-sm)]";}

!{boolean isBlocked = disabled || loading;}

<%-- SAFE dynamic data-* fragment (wireArgs win on key collision; pattern from button.jte).
     JTE's HTML parser forbids a raw @for in attribute-NAME position, so we build the fragment
     once and emit it with $unsafe -- safe because every dynamic VALUE is already escaped. --%>
!{var dataAttrsMerged = new java.util.LinkedHashMap<String, String>();}
!{dataAttrsMerged.putAll(dataAttrs);}
!{dataAttrsMerged.putAll(wireArgs);}
!{var dataAttrs_ = new StringOutput();}
!{for (var e : dataAttrsMerged.entrySet()) {
    if (e.getKey() != null && e.getKey().matches("[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9-]*")) {
      dataAttrs_.writeContent(" data-" + e.getKey() + "=\"");
      Escape.htmlAttribute(e.getValue() == null ? "" : e.getValue(), dataAttrs_);
      dataAttrs_.writeContent("\"");
    }
  }}
!{var dataAttrsMarkup = dataAttrs_.toString();}

<%-- Root wrapper: data-slot + data-size for test selectors and styling hooks. --%>
<div
  data-slot="switch-root"
  data-size="${size}"
  class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center gap-[var(--lv-space-2)] ${cssClass}"
  style="font-family:var(--lv-font-sans);"
>
  @if(leading != null)
    ${leading}
  @endif

  @if(asCheckbox)
    <%-- CHECKBOX VARIANT: <input type="checkbox" role="switch"> for form submission.
         Focus ring is expressed with has-[:focus-visible] on the outer span so it wraps
         the styled track; the input itself is sr-only (positioned off-screen) to preserve
         the native accessibility tree while allowing the custom track + thumb styling.
         Track colour: data-checked on this span mirrors the checked param for CSS targeting. --%>
    <span
      data-checked="${checked}"
      class="relative inline-flex shrink-0 ${trackClass} cursor-pointer items-center rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)] border border-[var(--lv-color-border)] bg-[var(--lv-color-input)] data-[checked=true]:border-[var(--lv-color-primary)] data-[checked=true]:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary)] transition-colors has-[:focus-visible]:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)] has-[:disabled]:cursor-not-allowed has-[:disabled]:opacity-[var(--lv-opacity-disabled)]"
    >
      <input
        data-slot="switch"
        type="checkbox"
        role="switch"
        name="${name}"
        value="${value}"
        checked="${checked}"
        disabled="${isBlocked}"
        aria-label="${ariaLabel}"
        aria-labelledby="${ariaLabelledBy}"
        aria-describedby="${ariaDescribedBy}"
        aria-busy="${loading ? "true" : null}"
        l:click="${(wireClick != null && !wireClick.isBlank()) ? wireClick : null}"
        $unsafe{dataAttrsMarkup}
        class="peer sr-only"
        $unsafe{attrs}
      >
      <%-- Thumb: peer-checked: from the sibling input drives translate + colour. --%>
      <span
        data-slot="switch-thumb"
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="pointer-events-none absolute left-[2px] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center ${thumbClass} rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)] bg-[var(--lv-color-fg)] shadow-[var(--lv-shadow-xs)] translate-x-0 ${thumbCheckboxCheckedClass} transition-[transform] duration-[var(--lv-duration-fast)] motion-reduce:transition-none"
      >
        @if(loading)
          @template.lievit.spinner(size = "sm", label = "Loading")
        @endif
      </span>
      <%-- Inner on/off labels (Ant Design style); aria-hidden avoids double-announcement. --%>
      @if(onLabel != null)
        <span
          class="switch-on-label pointer-events-none absolute ${onLabelLeft} hidden peer-checked:inline ${innerLabelSize} font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] text-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)] select-none"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >${onLabel}</span>
      @endif
      @if(offLabel != null)
        <span
          class="switch-off-label pointer-events-none absolute left-[4px] inline peer-checked:hidden ${innerLabelSize} font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] text-[var(--lv-color-muted)] select-none"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >${offLabel}</span>
      @endif
    </span>
  @else
    <%-- BUTTON VARIANT: <button role="switch"> -- the primary APG pattern.
         aria-checked="true|false" reflects the checked state for AT.
         Track colour + thumb translate: data-checked on this button drives
         data-[checked=true]: selectors on itself (track) and its children (thumb, labels).
         Destructive context: consumer adds `lv-switch--destructive` via cssClass; the
         [.lv-switch--destructive_&] selector overrides the checked track to the destructive token
         pair. --%>
    <button
      data-slot="switch"
      data-checked="${checked}"
      role="switch"
      type="button"
      aria-checked="${checked ? "true" : "false"}"
      aria-label="${ariaLabel}"
      aria-labelledby="${ariaLabelledBy}"
      aria-describedby="${ariaDescribedBy}"
      aria-busy="${loading ? "true" : null}"
      disabled="${isBlocked}"
      l:click="${(wireClick != null && !wireClick.isBlank()) ? wireClick : null}"
      $unsafe{dataAttrsMarkup}
      class="relative inline-flex shrink-0 ${trackClass} cursor-pointer items-center rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)] border border-[var(--lv-color-border)] bg-[var(--lv-color-input)] data-[checked=true]:border-[var(--lv-color-primary)] data-[checked=true]:bg-[var(--lv-color-primary)] transition-colors outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)] disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-[var(--lv-opacity-disabled)]"
      $unsafe{attrs}
    >
      <%-- Thumb: data-[checked=true] on the parent <button> drives translate + colour. --%>
      <span
        data-slot="switch-thumb"
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="pointer-events-none absolute left-[2px] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center ${thumbClass} rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)] bg-[var(--lv-color-fg)] shadow-[var(--lv-shadow-xs)] translate-x-0 ${thumbButtonCheckedClass} transition-[transform] duration-[var(--lv-duration-fast)] motion-reduce:transition-none"
      >
        @if(loading)
          @template.lievit.spinner(size = "sm", label = "Loading")
        @endif
      </span>
      <%-- Inner on/off labels (Ant Design style); aria-hidden avoids double-announcement.
           [[data-checked=true]_&]: targets an ancestor with data-checked=true (the parent button). --%>
      @if(onLabel != null)
        <span
          class="switch-on-label pointer-events-none absolute ${onLabelLeft} hidden [[data-checked=true]_&]:inline ${innerLabelSize} font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] text-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)] select-none"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >${onLabel}</span>
      @endif
      @if(offLabel != null)
        <span
          class="switch-off-label pointer-events-none absolute left-[4px] inline [[data-checked=true]_&]:hidden ${innerLabelSize} font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] text-[var(--lv-color-muted)] select-none"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >${offLabel}</span>
      @endif
    </button>
  @endif

  @if(trailing != null)
    ${trailing}
  @endif
</div>

@import gg.jte.output.StringOutput
@import gg.jte.html.escape.Escape
@import java.util.List
@import java.util.Collections
<%--
  Copyright 2026 Francesco Bilotta
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License").

  lievit-ui tabs partial -- WAI-ARIA APG Tabs: a role=tablist strip of role=tab triggers +
  their role=tabpanel regions, controlled/uncontrolled headless primitive.

  TIER: PARTIAL + ENH (collection-nav.enhancer.ts, roving-tabindex mode for the tablist).
  CONTROLLED/UNCONTROLLED doctrine (architecture-contract §Overlay & stateful primitives):
    - UNCONTROLLED (default, zero-JS-degradable): the caller renders the full DOM with all panels;
      client-side visibility is driven by the aria-selected/hidden state the server stamps on
      initial render. Changing the active tab requires a server round-trip via the caller's own
      wire action. The collection-nav enhancer manages roving tabindex + arrow-key focus, and in
      automatic-activation mode also fires the wire action on arrow press. This partial does NOT
      own a @Wire field and does NOT have a Java component.
    - CONTROLLED: the caller passes activeTab from its own @Wire field:
        activeTab = _instance.activeTab()
      The server then re-renders this partial with the new activeTab after the wire round-trip,
      and the bespoke morph patches the DOM. Same template, same params -- only the caller owns
      the state.

  STRUCTURE (WAI-ARIA APG Tabs https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/ +
  react-aria useTabList/useTab/useTabPanel interaction model as pattern reference (keyboard map,
  ARIA wiring, focus order; no source copied) + Ant Design Tabs as inventory reference
  (sizes, card/line/pill types, icon tabs, closable tabs, addable, lazy/eager panels)):
    root:    data-slot="tabs" data-orientation data-type data-size flex container;
    tablist: role="tablist" aria-label|aria-labelledby aria-orientation;
             data-lievit-collection (activates collection-nav enhancer, roving-tabindex mode);
    tabs:    real <button role="tab"> (native keyboard activation; NOT <a> or <div>);
             aria-selected aria-controls tabindex=0|-1 data-lievit-item;
    panels:  role="tabpanel" id="panel-{tabsId}-{tabId}" aria-labelledby="tab-{tabsId}-{tabId}"
             tabindex="0" (when no focusable children); eager: hidden="${!active}";
             lazy: inactive placeholder carries hx-get + hx-swap="outerHTML" + hx-trigger.

  A11y (WAI-ARIA APG Tabs, https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/):
    roles:   [role=tablist aria-label|aria-labelledby aria-orientation] >
             [role=tab id="tab-{tabsId}-{tabId}" aria-selected="true|false"
              aria-controls="panel-{tabsId}-{tabId}" tabindex="0|-1"
              aria-disabled="true" (disabled only; NOT native disabled -- a disabled tab MUST
              remain focusable in the roving order per APG)] +
             [role=tabpanel id="panel-{tabsId}-{tabId}" aria-labelledby="tab-{tabsId}-{tabId}"
              tabindex="0" when no focusable children]
    keys:    ArrowRight/Left (horizontal) | ArrowDown/Up (vertical) -- collection-nav roving;
             Home/End -- collection-nav; Enter/Space (manual mode) -- collection-nav;
             Tab -- platform: exits tablist into active tabpanel (next tabindex=0 element).
    disabled: aria-disabled="true" ONLY. Native disabled removes from tab order (breaks APG).
    close:   icon-only <button aria-label="Close {label}"> inside each closable tab (required).
    add:     icon-only <button aria-label="Add tab"> trailing the tablist (required).
    panel tabindex: tabindex="0" default; adopter drops it when the panel has focusable children.

  collection-nav attributes on the tablist root:
    data-lievit-collection                         -- activates the enhancer
    data-lievit-collection-roving-tabindex="true"  -- selects APG Tabs roving-tabindex model
    data-lievit-collection-orientation             -- "horizontal" | "vertical"
    data-lievit-collection-wrap="true"             -- wrap at ends (APG Tabs default)
    data-lievit-collection-select-action           -- wire action fired on Enter/Space (manual)
                                                      or on arrow key (automatic) by the enhancer
    data-manual-activation                         -- "true" = manual (arrow=focus only,
                                                      Enter/Space=activate); absent = automatic

  WIRE channels (XSS decision rule; same as button.jte):
    attrs     = TRUSTED raw ($unsafe) -- STATIC author-typed strings ONLY (e.g. data-testid).
                NEVER interpolate a per-tab id or user-derived value into attrs.
    Per-tab ids go through Escape.htmlAttribute and are emitted via $unsafe after escaping
    (the wireArgs / dataAttrs pattern from button.jte / switch.jte).

  Params:
    String tabsId             REQUIRED. A unique id for this tabset on the page; used to
                              derive deterministic ARIA anchor ids (tab-{tabsId}-{tabId},
                              panel-{tabsId}-{tabId}). Must be URL-safe, no spaces. When the
                              caller uses a wire component it typically passes the component id.
    List<String> tabIds       ordered tab id slugs. index-aligned with tabLabels, tabIcons,
                              tabClosable, tabDisabled.
    List<String> tabLabels    visible tab labels (index-aligned with tabIds).
    List<String> tabIcons     icon names per tab; empty string = no icon (index-aligned,
                              may be shorter -- missing entries default to no icon).
    List<Boolean> tabClosable whether each tab shows the close button (index-aligned;
                              may be shorter -- missing entries default to false).
    List<Boolean> tabDisabled whether each tab carries aria-disabled (index-aligned;
                              may be shorter -- missing entries default to false).
    String activeTab          the id of the currently active tab (server truth).
    String orientation = "horizontal"  "horizontal" | "vertical".
    String size = "md"        "sm" | "md" | "lg" (tab height, toolbar-aligned).
    String type = "line"      "line" | "card" | "pill".
    boolean lazyLoad = false  false = eager (all panels in DOM, hidden); true = HTMX lazy swap.
    boolean addable = false   show "add tab" + button trailing the tablist.
    boolean manualActivation = false  APG activation mode. false = automatic (arrow = focus +
                              activate); true = manual (arrow = focus only; Enter/Space = activate).
    String tabsLabel = null   aria-label for the tablist (REQUIRED unless tabsLabelledBy is set).
    String tabsLabelledBy = null  aria-labelledby alternative to tabsLabel.
    String selectAction = null  wire action name fired by collection-nav on tab activation
                              (emitted on the tab button element; the enhancer reads it from
                              data-lievit-collection-select-action on the tablist root). Typically
                              the caller's activate(id) action name -- e.g. "activate".
    String closeAction = null  wire action name for the close button l:click (caller's closeTab).
    String addAction = null    wire action name for the add button l:click (caller's addTab).
    String cssClass = ""      extra utility classes on the root.
    String attrs = ""         TRUSTED raw attribute string ($unsafe) -- STATIC strings only.

  Usage (controlled -- caller owns activeTab):
    @@template.lievit.tabs(
      tabsId       = _component.id(),
      tabIds       = java.util.List.of("info", "docs", "history"),
      tabLabels    = java.util.List.of("Anagrafica", "Documenti", "Storico"),
      tabIcons     = java.util.List.of("user", "", "clock"),
      tabClosable  = java.util.List.of(false, true, true),
      tabDisabled  = java.util.List.of(false, false, false),
      activeTab    = activeTab,
      tabsLabel    = "Settings",
      selectAction = "activate",
      closeAction  = "closeTab",
      addAction    = "addTab",
      addable      = true
    )
    Then in the caller's WIRE template body: author each panel region as
    data-slot="tabs-content" divs (owned markup; no Content slot per server-first blueprint).
--%>
@param String tabsId
@param List<String> tabIds
@param List<String> tabLabels
@param List<String> tabIcons = Collections.emptyList()
@param List<Boolean> tabClosable = Collections.emptyList()
@param List<Boolean> tabDisabled = Collections.emptyList()
@param String activeTab
@param String orientation = "horizontal"
@param String size = "md"
@param String type = "line"
@param boolean lazyLoad = false
@param boolean addable = false
@param boolean manualActivation = false
@param String tabsLabel = null
@param String tabsLabelledBy = null
@param String selectAction = null
@param String closeAction = null
@param String addAction = null
@param String cssClass = ""
@param String attrs = ""

<%-- ── Height token per size: toolbar-alignment rule (same scale as button.jte).
     sm -> --lv-space-8 (32px) | md -> --lv-space-9 (36px) | lg -> --lv-space-10 (40px). --%>
!{var heightClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "h-[var(--lv-space-8)]";
    case "lg" -> "h-[var(--lv-space-10)]";
    default   -> "h-[var(--lv-space-9)]";
  };}

<%-- ── Horizontal padding proportional to size (same rule as button.jte). --%>
!{var hPadClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "px-[var(--lv-space-4)]";
    default   -> "px-[var(--lv-space-6)]";
  };}

<%-- ── Text size per size. --%>
!{var textClass = switch (size) {
    case "sm" -> "text-[length:var(--lv-text-sm)]";
    default   -> "text-[length:var(--lv-text-base)]";
  };}

<%-- ── Tablist strip style by type.
     line: bottom divider below the strip (border-b on the tablist wrapper); active tab spans it
           with -mb-px so the indicator merges with the strip divider visually.
     card: raised card tabs; no strip divider; active card has no bottom border (merges with panel).
     pill: filled background pill on active tab; no strip divider. --%>
!{var stripClass = switch (type) {
    case "pill" -> "flex items-center gap-[var(--lv-space-1)] overflow-x-auto";
    case "card" -> "flex items-end gap-[var(--lv-space-1)] overflow-x-auto";
    default     -> "flex items-stretch gap-[var(--lv-space-1)] overflow-x-auto border-b border-[var(--lv-color-border)]";
  };}

<%-- ── Shared tab button base (all types).
     NOTE: no native `disabled` -- disabled tabs use aria-disabled only per APG (native disabled
     removes the element from the tab order, which breaks the APG roving-tabindex model). --%>
!{var tabBase = "inline-flex shrink-0 items-center gap-[var(--lv-space-3)] whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer border outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-[var(--lv-duration-fast)] focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)] aria-disabled:opacity-50 aria-disabled:cursor-not-allowed font-[family-name:var(--lv-font-sans)]";}

<%-- ── ACTIVE tab visual per type.
     line: fg label + font-medium + primary border-bottom indicator + -mb-px to span strip divider.
     card: bg surface (merges with panel), fg label, font-medium, card border, no bottom border,
           top rounding, shadow-xs.
     pill: primary background, primary-fg label, font-medium, full rounding. --%>
!{var activeTabLine = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " text-[var(--lv-color-fg)] font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] border-transparent border-b-2 border-b-[var(--lv-color-primary)] -mb-px rounded-none";}
!{var activeTabCard = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " bg-[var(--lv-color-bg)] text-[var(--lv-color-fg)] font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] border border-[var(--lv-color-border)] border-b-[var(--lv-color-bg)] shadow-[var(--lv-shadow-xs)] rounded-t-[var(--lv-radius-md)] rounded-b-none";}
!{var activeTabPill = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " bg-[var(--lv-color-primary)] text-[var(--lv-color-primary-fg)] font-[var(--lv-font-medium)] border-transparent rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)]";}

<%-- ── INACTIVE tab visual per type.
     line: muted label, transparent border, no rounding; hover: accent bg + accent-fg label.
     card: card bg, muted label, card border, shadow-xs, top rounding; hover: accent tint.
     pill: transparent bg + border, muted label; hover: accent bg + accent-fg label. --%>
!{var inactiveTabLine = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)] border-transparent rounded-none hover:bg-[var(--lv-color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--lv-color-accent-fg)]";}
!{var inactiveTabCard = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " bg-[var(--lv-color-card)] text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)] border border-[var(--lv-color-border)] shadow-[var(--lv-shadow-xs)] rounded-t-[var(--lv-radius-md)] rounded-b-none hover:bg-[var(--lv-color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--lv-color-accent-fg)]";}
!{var inactiveTabPill = heightClass + " " + hPadClass + " bg-transparent text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)] border-transparent rounded-[var(--lv-radius-full)] hover:bg-[var(--lv-color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--lv-color-accent-fg)]";}

<%-- ── collection-nav orientation: maps orientation param to the enhancer's attribute value. --%>
!{var collNavOrientation = "vertical".equals(orientation) ? "vertical" : "horizontal";}

<%-- ── Root flex direction: horizontal tablist = column (strip above panels);
     vertical tablist = row (strip beside panels). --%>
!{var rootDirClass = "vertical".equals(orientation) ? "flex-row" : "flex-col";}

<%-- ── selectAction attr value: emit as non-null string when set, null = omit the attribute. --%>
!{var selectActionAttr = (selectAction != null && !selectAction.isBlank()) ? selectAction : null;}

<div
  data-slot="tabs"
  data-orientation="${orientation}"
  data-type="${type}"
  data-size="${size}"
  class="flex ${rootDirClass} font-[family-name:var(--lv-font-sans)] ${cssClass}"
  $unsafe{attrs}
>
  <%-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ tablist strip ══ --%>
  <div
    role="tablist"
    aria-label="${tabsLabel}"
    aria-labelledby="${tabsLabelledBy}"
    aria-orientation="${orientation}"
    data-slot="tabs-list"
    data-lievit-collection
    data-lievit-collection-roving-tabindex="true"
    data-lievit-collection-orientation="${collNavOrientation}"
    data-lievit-collection-wrap="true"
    data-lievit-collection-select-action="${selectActionAttr}"
    data-manual-activation="${manualActivation ? "true" : null}"
    class="${stripClass}"
  >
    @for(int i = 0; i < tabIds.size(); i++)
      !{var tabId = tabIds.get(i);}
      !{var tabLabel = i < tabLabels.size() ? tabLabels.get(i) : tabId;}
      !{var tabIcon = i < tabIcons.size() ? tabIcons.get(i) : "";}
      !{var isClosable = i < tabClosable.size() && Boolean.TRUE.equals(tabClosable.get(i));}
      !{var isDisabled = i < tabDisabled.size() && Boolean.TRUE.equals(tabDisabled.get(i));}
      !{var isActive = tabId.equals(activeTab);}

      <%-- Escape per-tab id through Escape.htmlAttribute: tab ids are server-supplied and
           potentially user-influenced; they MUST go through the SAFE escaped channel, never
           through the trusted $unsafe `attrs` channel (XSS decision rule). --%>
      !{var safeIdOut = new StringOutput();}
      !{Escape.htmlAttribute(tabId, safeIdOut);}
      !{var safeTabId = safeIdOut.toString();}

      <%-- Escape tab label for use in aria-label of the close button. --%>
      !{var safeLabelOut = new StringOutput();}
      !{Escape.htmlAttribute(tabLabel, safeLabelOut);}
      !{var safeTabLabel = safeLabelOut.toString();}

      <%-- Per-type active/inactive class for this tab. --%>
      !{var tabStateClass = isActive
          ? switch (type) {
              case "card" -> activeTabCard;
              case "pill" -> activeTabPill;
              default     -> activeTabLine;
            }
          : switch (type) {
              case "card" -> inactiveTabCard;
              case "pill" -> inactiveTabPill;
              default     -> inactiveTabLine;
            };}

      <%-- WAI-ARIA APG Tabs: each tab is a real <button role="tab">.
           tabindex="0" on the active tab; tabindex="-1" on all others (roving tabindex;
           collection-nav updates on arrow-key navigation).
           aria-disabled="true" on disabled tabs; NOT native `disabled` (a disabled tab must
           remain focusable in the roving order per APG; native disabled breaks that by removing
           the element from the tab order). The Java action and the collection-nav enhancer both
           enforce no-activation for disabled tabs.
           l:click fires the caller's wire action when selectAction is set. The data-id carries
           the tab id through the SAFE escaped channel (never through $unsafe attrs). --%>
      <%-- The tab trigger and its close button are SIBLINGS inside a presentation wrapper, never
           nested: a <button> inside a <button> is invalid HTML and a click target ambiguity. The
           role=tab + data-lievit-item live on the trigger; collection-nav finds the item at any
           depth; the close button is outside the tab's activation area (closing != selecting). --%>
      <span data-slot="tabs-trigger-wrapper" role="presentation" class="relative inline-flex items-center">
        <button
          type="button"
          role="tab"
          id="tab-${tabsId}-$unsafe{safeTabId}"
          aria-selected="${isActive ? "true" : "false"}"
          aria-controls="panel-${tabsId}-$unsafe{safeTabId}"
          aria-disabled="${isDisabled ? "true" : null}"
          tabindex="${isActive ? "0" : "-1"}"
          data-slot="tabs-trigger"
          data-lievit-item
          data-id="$unsafe{safeTabId}"
          l:click="${selectActionAttr}"
          class="${tabBase} ${tabStateClass} ${textClass}"
        >
          @if(tabIcon != null && !tabIcon.isBlank())
            @template.lievit.icon(name = tabIcon, size = "1em")
          @endif
          ${tabLabel}
        </button>
        @if(isClosable)
          <%-- Icon-only close button: aria-label="Close {label}" is REQUIRED (an icon-only button
               with no accessible name is unusable to AT). data-id carries the tab id through the
               SAFE escaped channel; the runtime dispatches l:click on this element independently. --%>
          !{var closeIdOut = new StringOutput();}
          !{Escape.htmlAttribute(tabId, closeIdOut);}
          !{var safeCloseId = closeIdOut.toString();}
          !{var closeAction2 = (closeAction != null && !closeAction.isBlank()) ? closeAction : null;}
          <button
            type="button"
            aria-label="Close $unsafe{safeTabLabel}"
            data-slot="tabs-close"
            data-id="$unsafe{safeCloseId}"
            l:click="${closeAction2}"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 w-[var(--lv-space-4)] h-[var(--lv-space-4)] -ml-[var(--lv-space-1)] mr-[var(--lv-space-1)] p-0 rounded-[var(--lv-radius-md)] border-transparent bg-transparent cursor-pointer text-inherit hover:bg-[var(--lv-color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--lv-color-accent-fg)] outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)] transition-[color,background-color,box-shadow] duration-[var(--lv-duration-fast)]"
          >@template.lievit.icon(name = "x", size = "0.75em")</button>
        @endif
      </span>
    @endfor

    @if(addable)
      <%-- Icon-only add-tab button: aria-label="Add tab" is REQUIRED (no visible text, WAI-ARIA
           button rule). This button does NOT carry data-lievit-item: it is not a tab in the
           tablist; it is a trailing action outside the roving focus order. The platform's natural
           Tab order reaches it after the tablist's active tab without special wiring. --%>
      !{var addActionAttr = (addAction != null && !addAction.isBlank()) ? addAction : null;}
      !{var addBtnWidthClass = switch (size) {
          case "sm" -> "w-[var(--lv-space-8)]";
          case "lg" -> "w-[var(--lv-space-10)]";
          default   -> "w-[var(--lv-space-9)]";
        };}
      <button
        type="button"
        aria-label="Add tab"
        data-slot="tabs-add"
        l:click="${addActionAttr}"
        class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center ${heightClass} ${addBtnWidthClass} p-0 ml-[var(--lv-space-1)] border border-transparent rounded-[var(--lv-radius-md)] bg-transparent text-[var(--lv-color-muted-fg)] cursor-pointer hover:bg-[var(--lv-color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--lv-color-accent-fg)] outline-none focus-visible:shadow-[var(--lv-ring)] transition-[color,background-color,box-shadow] duration-[var(--lv-duration-fast)]"
      >@template.lievit.icon(name = "plus", size = "1em")</button>
    @endif
  </div>

  <%-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ panels ══ --%>
  @for(int p = 0; p < tabIds.size(); p++)
    !{var ptTabId = tabIds.get(p);}
    !{var ptIsActive = ptTabId.equals(activeTab);}

    <%-- Escape panel tab id (same SAFE channel as above). --%>
    !{var ptSafeOut = new StringOutput();}
    !{Escape.htmlAttribute(ptTabId, ptSafeOut);}
    !{var ptSafeId = ptSafeOut.toString();}

    @if(lazyLoad && !ptIsActive)
      <%-- LAZY PANEL PLACEHOLDER (inactive tabs, lazy mode).
           No body content is rendered here; HTMX swaps in the real fragment when
           the "tabs-activate" custom event fires (dispatched by the runtime afterCall hook
           after the wire round-trip re-renders with the new activeTab).
           The minimal tabpanel shell keeps the ARIA relationship (aria-labelledby) present in
           the DOM before the swap so AT can traverse the full tab structure without triggering
           a load. hx-swap="outerHTML" replaces this placeholder with the real panel element.
           After first load the panel stays in the DOM (hidden) so back-navigation is instant. --%>
      <div
        role="tabpanel"
        id="panel-${tabsId}-$unsafe{ptSafeId}"
        aria-labelledby="tab-${tabsId}-$unsafe{ptSafeId}"
        data-slot="tabs-content"
        hidden
        hx-get="/tabs/${tabsId}/panel/$unsafe{ptSafeId}"
        hx-swap="outerHTML"
        hx-trigger="tabs-activate from:closest [data-slot='tabs']"
      ></div>
    @else
      <%-- EAGER PANEL (lazyLoad=false) or the ACTIVE PANEL in lazy mode.
           hidden="${!ptIsActive}" removes inactive panels from view + the a11y tree (boolean
           attribute: the string "false" is a truthy boolean attribute in HTML5, so we rely on
           JTE's boolean-attribute smart-attr here: hidden="${!ptIsActive}" emits the bare
           `hidden` attribute when ptIsActive is false and omits it when ptIsActive is true).
           tabindex="0" is the DEFAULT: the tabpanel must be keyboard-reachable after Tab exits
           the tablist (APG requirement when the panel body has no focusable children). The
           adopter DROPS tabindex on this element when the panel body contains interactive
           children (focus lands naturally on the first child instead).
           outline-none suppresses the default :focus ring on the panel (it is a focus stop for
           screen readers, not a visually-interactive element). --%>
      <div
        role="tabpanel"
        id="panel-${tabsId}-$unsafe{ptSafeId}"
        aria-labelledby="tab-${tabsId}-$unsafe{ptSafeId}"
        tabindex="0"
        data-slot="tabs-content"
        hidden="${!ptIsActive}"
        class="p-[var(--lv-space-4)] outline-none"
      >
        <%-- OWNED BODY REGION for this panel. The caller places server-rendered panel markup
             here after copying in the template. This is the server-first "owned content" model:
             no JTE Content slot (the headless controlled/uncontrolled contract has none), no
             <slot> (eliminates the silent-slot bug class the pivot killed). Panel bodies are
             plain server-rendered HTML, authored by the adopter per-tab.
             Default placeholder (replace with real content in your adopted copy): --%>
        <p data-tabs-body="${ptTabId}">Panel content for ${tabIds.get(p)}.</p>
      </div>
    @endif
  @endfor
</div>

